Imran%20Khan%20end%20though.%20Suhrawardy%20was%20an%20intellectual%20and%20political%20giant%20who%20stood%20firmly%20for%20parliamentary%20democracy%2C%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Farticles%2Fpakistan%2F1957-04-01%2Fpolitical-stability-and-democracy-pakistan%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Farticles%2Fpakistan%2F1957-04-01%2Fpolitical-stability-and-democracy-pakistan%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707374941341000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0_iONb90v5e78OPJekiqxI%5C%22%3Epluralist%20nation%20state%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20refused%20to%20endorse%20military%20rule.%C2%A0Imran%20Khan%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20is%20an%20authoritarian%20demagogue%20who%20was%20handpicked%2C%20groomed%2C%20installed%20into%20the%20high%20office%2C%20and%20sustained%20there%20by%20the%20army%20till%20they%20fell%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20imposing%20martial%20law%20four%20times%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20army%20has%20ruled%20indirectly%20for%20most%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20existence.%20To%20that%20end%2C%20the%20junta%20has%20manipulated%20the%20political%20process%20by%20creating%20or%20co-opting%20what%20it%20deemed%20%E2%80%98patriotic%E2%80%99%20and%20pliant%20individuals%20and%20parties.%20The%20army%E2%80%99s%20chosen%20politicians%2C%20however%2C%20have%20invariably%20spun%20out%20of%20its%20orbit%20like%20Zulfikar%20Ali%20Bhutto%2C%20and%20some%20even%20locked%20horns%20with%20the%20brass%2C%20like%20Nawaz%20Sharif.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20all%20ultimately%20paid%20the%20price%20for%20standing%20up%20to%20the%20army.%20And%20Imran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20fate%20was%20not%20going%20to%20be%20any%20different.%20Chairman%20Mao%20Zedong%20had%20famously%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Party%20commands%20the%20gun%2C%20and%20the%20gun%20must%20never%20be%20allowed%20to%20command%20the%20Party%E2%80%9D.%20The%20gist%20of%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20perennial%20civil-military%20imbalance%20is%20that%20those%20wielding%20the%20guns%20clearly%20believe%20that%20no%20political%20party%20%E2%80%93%20including%20the%20assorted%20king%E2%80%99s%20parties%20that%20they%20sired%20themselves%20%E2%80%93%20should%20ever%20be%20allowed%20to%20command%20the%20gun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Frigged-or-not-polls-are-the-only-option-for-pakistan%5C%22%3ERigged%20or%20Not%2C%20Polls%20Are%20the%20Only%20Option%20for%20Pakistan%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20when%20in%20late%202021%2C%20then%20PM%20Imran%20Khan%20tried%20to%20assert%20himself%20and%20insisted%20on%20retaining%20his%20closest%20ally%20Lt.%20General%20Faiz%20Hameed%20in%20place%20as%20the%20director%20general%20of%20the%20ISI%2C%20the%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%20(COAS)%20General%20Qamar%20Javed%20Bajwa%20stonewalled%20him.%20Never%20mind%20that%20General%20Bajwa%20had%20himself%20presided%20over%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpakistan-elections-imran-khan%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fpakistan-elections-imran-khan%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707374941341000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw2ejl2YSCVo_wbzwG5zuZ9w%5C%22%3EImran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20installation%20into%20high%20office%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20an%20arrangement%20called%20the%20hybrid%20regime.%20By%20that%20time%20Imran%20Khan%20had%20already%20been%20losing%20the%20confidence%20and%20support%20of%20the%20military%20establishment%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20a%20horrifying%20mismanagement%20of%20the%20economy%20and%20shoddy%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F05165322%2FEWTbl5GWsAclor5.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F05165322%2FEWTbl5GWsAclor5.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F05165322%2FEWTbl5GWsAclor5-300x168.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F05165322%2FEWTbl5GWsAclor5-1024x573.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-520691%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22671%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFormer%20Pakistani%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan%20with%20Chief%20of%20Army%20Staff%20General%20Qamar%20Javed%20Bajwa.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2FPTIofficial%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20generals%20who%20were%20rightly%20getting%20blamed%20for%20imposing%20and%20sustaining%20the%20disastrous%20Imran%20Khan%20project%2C%20decided%20to%20change%20horses.%20The%20opposition%20political%20parties%20saw%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20proclamation%20that%20it%20would%20stay%20politically%20neutral%2C%20as%20a%20nod%20to%20lunge%20at%20Imran%20Khan.%20In%20April%202022%2C%20a%20rainbow%20coalition%20called%20the%20Pakistan%20Democratic%20Movement%20(PDM)%2C%20which%20included%20parties%20like%20the%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PMLN)%20and%20Jamiat-e-Ulama-e-Islam%2C%20supported%20by%20the%20Pakistan%20Peoples%20Party%20(PPP)%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fas-imran-loses-trust-vote-shehbaz-sharif-emerges-frontrunner-for-pak-pms-post%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fas-imran-loses-trust-vote-shehbaz-sharif-emerges-frontrunner-for-pak-pms-post%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1707374941341000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw1P5793HefhdJBqY35T7sCe%5C%22%3Eousted%20Imran%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20his%20Pakistan%20Tehrik-e-Insaf%20(PTI)%20party%E2%80%99s%20government%20through%20a%C2%A0%3C