businessinsider.com%2Fmanmade-object-satellite-outshines-nearly-every-star-night-sky-space-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einternet-satellite%20constellations%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20an%20existential%20threat.%20But%20of%20all%20the%20companies%20racing%20to%20claim%20this%20new%20frontier%2C%20SpaceX%20has%20calmed%20some%20of%20its%20critics%20by%20listening%20to%20them%2C%20working%20with%20them%2C%20and%20trying%20to%20darken%20its%20satellites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20we're%20making%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20Jonathan%20McDowell%2C%20an%20astronomer%20who%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20most%20outspoken%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starlink-internet-satellites-percent-failure-rate-space-debris-risk-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStarlink's%20critics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20at%20a%20conference%20of%20the%20American%20Astronomical%20Society%20in%20New%20Orleans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22three%20white%20satellite%20lines%20streak%20across%20black%20and%20white%20image%20of%20starry%20universe%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64013c81934c2c001802756e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224096%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThree%20different%20satellite%20trails%20outshine%20the%20stars%20in%20an%20image%20from%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FESA%2FKruk%20et%20al.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMcDowell%20and%20other%20astronomers%20were%20meeting%20with%20representatives%20from%20the%20satellite%20industry%20to%20discuss%20efforts%20to%20keep%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarkest-skies-by-state-watch-space-events-stargazing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskies%20dark%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20radio-quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20current%20SpaceX%20representative%20participated%20in%20the%20session.%20Still%2C%20Starlink's%20experimental%20solutions%20dominated%20the%20conversation%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20because%20it's%20the%20only%20company%20that's%20been%20trying%20the%20fixes%20astronomers%20have%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%20the%20focus%20is%20not%20on%20the%20call%20to%20alarm%20only%2C%20it's%20on%20the%20path%20to%20coexistence%2C%26quot%3B%20Patricia%20Cooper%2C%20a%20satellite-industry%20consultant%20who%20was%20formerly%20VP%20of%20SpaceX's%20government%20affairs%20for%20satellites%2C%20told%20the%20assembled%20astronomers.%20%26quot%3BNot%20surprisingly%2C%20we%20didn't%20solve%20the%20problem%20in%20four%20and%20a%20half%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESpaceX%20has%20tried%20black%20paint%2C%20sun%20visors%2C%20and%20now%20'mirror%20film'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6569c45d58e7c0c29a289d99%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECEO%20Elon%20Musk%20has%20said%20little%20publicly%20about%20astronomers'%20concerns%2C%20but%20SpaceX%20has%20worked%20with%20astronomy%20leaders%20privately.%3Cp%3ESlaven%20Vlasic%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20thrown%20a%20handful%20of%20spaghetti%20at%20the%20wall%20to%20dim%20its%20satellites'%20shine%2C%20and%20a%20few%20things%20have%20stuck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20about%20six%20months%20after%20that%20first%20bright%20Starlink%20trail%20glided%20through%20the%20skies%2C%20SpaceX%20lobbed%20its%20first%20noodle%20at%20the%20problem%20by%20essentially%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-darkened-starlink-internet-satellites-astronomy-explainer-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epainting%20a%20bunch%20of%20the%20satellites%20black%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20sort%20of%20helped.%20The%20satellites%20were%20less%20bright%2C%20but%20they%20were%20still%20too%20bright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspacex-starlink-sun-shades-visors-cut-reflection-telescope-problems-remain-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20tried%20using%20sun%20visors%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20block%20sunlight%20from%20hitting%20the%20bottom%20side%20of%20the%20satellites%2C%20where%20it%20can%20reflect%20back%20to%20Earth%20and%20make%20them%20appear%20bright.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20worked.%20The%20visored%20satellites%20were%20about%20one-third%20as%20bright%20as%20those%20that%20launched%20without%20visors.%20But%20they%20were%20still%20bright%20enough%20to%20mess%20with%20astronomers'%20data.%20The%20visors%20were%20a%20regular%20feature%20for%20many%20Starlink%20satellites%20until%20SpaceX%20added%20laser%20communications.%20The%20visors%20blocked%20the%20lasers%2C%20so%20they%20had%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20SpaceX%20is%20looking%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bmirror%20film%26quot%3B%20that%20could%20further%20reduce%20brightness%20on%20its%20next%20Starlink%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egeneration.%20However%2C%20those%20satellites%20are%20much%20bigger%20than%20the%20old%20ones%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20it%20kind%20of%20cancels%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20McDowell%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20there%20are%20all%20villain%20or%20all%20hero%20things%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20developed%20its%20solutions%20through%20meetings%20with%20astronomers%2C%20including%20the%20world's%20first%20conference%20on%20satellite%20brightness.%20In%202022%2C%20the%20International%20Astronomical%20Union%20formalized%20this%20ongoing%20collaboration%20as%20the%20Centre%20for%20the%20Protection%20of%20the%20Dark%20and%20Quiet%20Sky%20from%20Satellite%20Constellation%20Interference%20%E2%80%94%20CPS%2C%20for%20short.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20has%20even%20adopted%20an%20operational%20tweak%20that%20astronomers%20suggested%20%E2%80%94%20pointing%20the%20satellites'%20solar%20panels%20away%20from%20the%20sun%20as%20they%20pass%20over%20the%20line%20between%20night%20and%20day.%20That's%20when%20they%20appear%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20and%20are%20most%20detrimental%20for%20telescopes%20on%20Earth.%20Giving%20the%20solar%20panels%20less%20sun%20at%20this%20time%20helps%20astronomers%2C%20but%20means%20less%20energy%20for%20the%20satellite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20real%2C%20substantial%20mitigation%20that%20they've%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20McDowell%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20really%20taking%20a%20money%20hit%20by%20doing%20that.%20So%20we%20appreciate%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-elon-musk-starlink-low-orbit-satellites-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eother%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20do%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAmazon%20and%20other%20companies%20may%20follow%20SpaceX's%20lead%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20and%20a%20small%20Earth-imaging%20company%20called%20Planet%20Labs%20are%20both%20following%20SpaceX's%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Hofer%2C%20international%20team%20lead%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-strikes-deal-with-spacex-for-satellite-launch-partnership-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon's%20Project%20Kuiper%3C%2Fa%3E%20internet%20satellites%2C%20told%20the%20astronomers%20in%20New%20Orleans%20that%20SpaceX's%20Starlink%20tinkering%20has%20been%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20joining%20CPS%2C%20Hofer%20said%20Amazon%20has%20begun%20improving%20its%20solar%20panels%20and%20looking%20into%20sun%20shades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20Hofer%20and%20Kristina%20Barkume%2C%20of%20the%20Earth-imaging%20satellite%20company%20Planet%2C%20said%20they%20would%20be%20following%20SpaceX's%20new%20mirror-film%20tests%20with%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20innovations%20help%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20