%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-elusive-smartness-in-indias-smart-cities%5C%22%3ESmart%20Cities%20Mission%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20envisioned%20as%20the%20lighthouse%20of%20city%20development.%20With%20a%20total%20of%20100%20cities%20included%20in%20its%20proposal%2C%20this%20flagship%20programme%20received%20budgetary%20support%20and%20continued%20to%20dominate%20urban%20planning%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20no%20mention%20of%20urban%20planning%20or%20cities%20in%20the%20Union%20budget%20speech.%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20concept%20of%20smart%20cities%20has%20faded%2C%20with%20only%20a%20passing%20reference%20to%20urbanisation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fhalf-of-countrys-population-will-be-living-in-cities-in-few-decades-union-minister-kaushal-kishore%2Farticleshow%2F106023424.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Etaking%20place%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20rapid%20pace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20the%20interim%20budget%20boasted%20of%20its%20revenue%20receipts%2C%20saying%20that%20there%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbudget%2Fbudget_parliament%2F2024%2FInterim_Union_Budget_Analysis-2024-25.pdf%5C%22%3Eincrease%20of%2011%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202024-25.%20However%2C%20the%20growth%20in%20revenue%20receipts%20is%20driven%20by%20corporate%20tax%20and%20income%20tax%2C%20which%20is%20estimated%20to%20grow%20by%2013%25%20each.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20between%202018-19%20and%202022-23%2C%20individual%20tax%20collections%20in%20India%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fk-shape-widens-govt-personal-income-tax-collection-corporate-tax%5C%22%3Ehave%20surged%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20a%20whopping%2076%25.%20However%2C%20the%20corporate%20sector%20share%20in%20that%20tax%20collected%20has%20inched%20by%20only%20a%20fraction%2C%20just%2024.45%25%2C%20during%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20implies%20that%20common%20people%20and%20the%20poor%20are%20contributing%20more%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20development.%20However%2C%20the%20dividends%20seem%20to%20be%20favouring%20corporates%2C%20as%20their%20tax%20percentage%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2F2022%2FAug%2F14%2Fin-first-two-years-of-corporate-tax-cut-govt-suffers-rs-184-lakh-crore-loss-2487445.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20reduced%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%2030%25%20to%2020%25%2C%20and%20even%2015%25%20in%20some%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20one%20looks%20at%20the%20expenditure%20part%2C%20Budget%202024-25%20is%20a%20sheer%20disaster.%20The%20social%20welfare%20expenditure%20has%20been%20reduced%20from%20the%20budgetary%20estimates%20of%202023-24%2C%20from%20Rs%202.42%20lakh%20crore%20to%20Rs%202.25%20lakh%20crore%20in%20revenue%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fgovernment-schemes-where-are-we-on-urban-agenda%5C%22%3EGovernment%20Schemes%3A%20Where%20Are%20We%20on%20Urban%20Agenda%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBudgetary%20allocation%20for%20urban%20areas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20urban%20domain%2C%20the%20situation%20is%20more%20pathetic.%20The%20total%20outlay%20falls%20far%20below%20expectations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20urban%20areas%20in%20the%20year%202023-24%20was%20Rs%2076%2C431%20crore.%20However%2C%20the%20revised%20estimate%20is%20approximately%20Rs%2069%2C270%20crore%2C%20indicating%20a%20shortfall%20of%20Rs%207%2C000%20crore.%20This%20shortfall%20should%20have%20been%20accommodated%20in%20the%20succeeding%20year%20of%202024-25.%20However%2C%20the%20total%20proposal%20for%202024-25%20stands%20at%20Rs%2077%2C525%20crore%2C%20just%201%25%20more%20than%20the%20previous%20year.%20Considering%20inflation%20and%20other%20factors%2C%20this%20suggests%20a%20decline%20in%20real%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20also%20find%20out%20where%20the%20shortfall%20has%20been%20in%20both%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiabudget.gov.in%2Fdoc%2Feb%2Fvol1.pdf%5C%22%3Erevised%20budget%20estimates%20and%20the%20proposal%20for%202024-25.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20massive%20shortfall%20of%20nearly%20Rs%206%2C000%20crore%20from%20the%20budgetary%20proposals%20and%20revised%20estimates%20of%202023-24.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20shortfall%20of%20around%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20in%20these%20schemes%20since%20last%20year.%20The%20figures%20are%20as%3A%20the%20proposal%20was%20Rs%2046%2C103%20crore%2C%20whereas%20the%20revised%20estimate%20is%20Rs%2038%2C396%20crore%20and%20the%20proposed%20outlay%20for%202024-25%20is%20Rs%2044%2C545%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20these%20schemes%2C%20it%20is%20interesting%20that%20around%20Rs%2019%2C518%20crore%20was%20allocated%20for%20metro%20rail%20projects%2C%20as%20per%20budget%20estimates%20of%202023-24%2C%20and%20in%20the%20current%20proposal%20of%202024-25%2C%20it%20stands%20at%20Rs%2021%2C335%20crore.%20That%20means%2048%25%20of%20the%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%20(in%20the%20urban%20category)%20will%20be%20usurped%20by%20the%20capital%20intensive%20metro%20projects%2C%20whereas%20the%20demand%20was%20for%20more%20buses%20in%20the%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20notable%20feature%20is%20a%20major%20setback%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20capital%20assets%20or%20urban%20infrastructure.%20There%20has%20been%20a%20drastic%20fall%20of%20around%20Rs%208%2C000%20crore%2C%20from%20Rs%2041%2C830%20crore%20as%20proposed%20in%20the%202023-24%20outlay%20to%20Rs%2033%2C779%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20outlay%20for%202024-25%20also%20remains%20lesser%20than%20the%20previous%20year%20at%20Rs%2039%2C861%20crore.%20Now%2C%20where%20is%20it%20that%20the%20budget%20could%20not%20be%20spent%20in%20the%20current%20fiscal%20year%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20the%20major%20fall%20has%20been%20in%20almost%20all%20the%20flagship%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20outlay%20in%20the%20Smart%20Cities%E2%80%99%20proposal%20fell%20from%20Rs%207%2C634%20crore%20to%20Rs%207%2C535%20crore%20in%20the%20revised%20budget%20of%202023-24%2C%20with%20a%20major%20slash%20in%20the%202024-25%20outlay%20to%20Rs%202%2C236%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELikewise%2C%20for%20AMRUT%2C%20the%20proposal%20sees%20a%20Rs%205%2C000%20cut%20from%20Rs%207%2C634%20crore%20to%20Rs%202%2C236%20crore%3B%20PMAY(U)%2C%20the%20housing%20trumpet%20being%20blown%20by%20the%20finance%20minister%2C%20also%20does%20not%20match%20the%20noise.%20The%20total%20outlay%20in%202023-24%20was%20Rs%2022%2C967%20crore%2C%20whereas%20the%20revised%20estimate%20is%20at%20Rs%2019%2C966%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20a%20shortfall%20of%20Rs%203%2C000%20crore.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20proposal%20for%202024-25%20is%20Rs%2023%2C920%20crore%2C%20which%20is%20just%201%25%20higher%20than%20the%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%20proposal.%20Considering%20inflation%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20construction%2C%20there%20is%20a%20downslide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Swachh%20Bharat%20Mission%2C%20which%20started%20in%20rocket%20mode%2C%20also%20fell%20from%20expectations.%20Against%20the%20total%20outlay%20of%20Rs%204%2C238%20crore%2C%20the%20revised%20estimate%20for%202023-24%20is%20at%20Rs%201%2C978%20crore%2C%20a%20fall%20of%20nearly%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%2C%20and%20a%20proposed%20figure%20of%20Rs%204%2C246%20crore%2C%20once%20again%20not%20even%20matching%20the%20previous%20year%E2%80%99s%20budgetary%20proposals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Funpaid-work-discouraged-workers-essential-services-as-gifts-jayati-ghosh-on-modi-govts-policies%5C%22%3EUnpaid%20Work%2C%20Discouraged%20Workers%2C%20Essential%20Services%20as%20%E2%80%98Gifts%E2%80%99%3A%20Jayati%20Ghosh%20on%20Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Policies%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPromises%20versus%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20finance%20minister%20used%20the%20terms%20%E2%80%9Chousing%2C%20water%2C%20sanitation%2C%20and%20finance%20for%20all%E2%80%9D%20in%20her%20remarks.%20But%20how%20does%20these%20items%20fare%20in%20the%20current%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%2C%20despite%20its%2010-year%20rule%20and%20promises%20of%20providing%20houses%20to%20everyone%20within%20the%20first%20five-year%20period%20from%202014%20to%202019%2C%20admits%20that%20there%20is%20still%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fbudget%2Fbudget-2024-new-housing-scheme-for-middle-class-to-propel-development-of-real-estate-3382092%2F%5C%22%3Eshortfall%20of%20nearly%2020%20million%20houses%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20rural%20areas.%20The%20urban%20figures%20have%20not%20been%20mentioned%2C%20but%20various%20estimates%20suggest%20that%20the%20figure%20is%20more%20than%20three%20million.%20How%20will%20this%20be%20addressed%3F%20As%20seen%20above%2C%20the%20figures%20belie%20the%20rhetoric.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20water%20supply%20and%20sanitation%20category%2C%20the%20figures%20remain%20static%20at%20Rs%2064%2C000%20crore%20under%20the%20revenue%20expenditure%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENeglecting%20the%20Himalayan%20states%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20notable%20feature%20of%20the%20current%20budgetary%20proposal%20is%20the%20complete%20absence%20of%20the%20Himalayan%20states.%20These%2013%20states%20have%20been%20demanding%20special%20financial%20packages%20and%20architecture%20owing%20to%20their%20extreme%20vulnerabilities%2C%20both%20climatic%20and%20geographic.%20It%20was%20expected%20that%20the%20government%20would%20assist%20these%20states%20in%20promoting%20tourism%20and%20allied%20sectors%2C%20such%20as%20fruit%20processing%20plants%2C%20agri-based%20allied%20help%20in%20the%20forms%20of%20procurement%2C%20and%20compressed%20atmosphere%20stores%2C%20which%20are%20capital-intensive%20technologies%20ensuring%20them%20a%20better%20livelihood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20linking%20their%20development%20models%20to%20climate%20change%20realities%20was%20anticipated.%20However%2C%20nothing%20has%20been%20said%20about%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reduction%20in%20apple%20import%20duty%20is%20negatively%20impacting%20farmers%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20and%20Uttarakhand%2C%20the%20three%20major%20apple-producing%20states.%20Fruit%20processing%20plants%20were%20considered%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20to%20mitigate%20the%20current%20challenges.%20However%2C%20the%20Himalayan%20mountains%20remain%20far%20beyond%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20centre%E2%80%99s%20financial%20assistance%20ambit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20budget%20resembles%20more%20of%20an%20election%20speech%2C%20eulogising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20rather%20than%20addressing%20the%20essentialities%20of%20the%20current%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETikender%20Singh%20Panwar%20was%20once%20directly%20elected%20deputy%20mayor%20of%20Shimla.%20He%20was%20linked%20with%20the%20Leh%20Vision%20document%20and%20has%20written%20vision%20documents%20for%20a%20dozen%20cities.%20Author%20of%20two%20books%2C%20he%20is%20an%20urban%20specialist%20working%20in%20the%20design%20of%20inclusive%20cities.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707307236000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F28151132%2FBudget-136445-pixahive.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fbleak-urban-outlay-neglected-himalayan-states-decoding-the-2024-budgets-election-rhetoric%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%2C%20there's%20a%20massive%20shortfall%20of%20nearly%20Rs%206%2C000%20crore%20from%20the%20budgetary%20proposals%20and%20revised%20estimates%20of%202023-24.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A13%2C%22canonicalUrl