hef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F10246%2Fproduction%2F_132581166_gettyimages-1243612746.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68225599%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Russia's%20two%20gas%20pipelines%20were%20sabotaged%20in%20September%202022%20and%20it%20is%20still%20unknown%20who%20is%20responsible.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A39%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68225599%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68225599.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-68225599.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22FMCG%20Growth%20Slows%20Sequentially%20in%20December%20Quarter%3B%20Expected%20to%20Slow%20to%204.5-6.5%25%20in%202024%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15171005%2F1024px-Supermarket_full_of_goods.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20fast-moving%20consumer%20goods%20(FMCG)%20sector%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20at%204.5-6.5%25%20in%202024%2C%20sharply%20lower%20than%20the%20robust%209.3%25%20growth%20experienced%20in%202023%20and%208.4%25%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbctv18.com%2Fbusiness%2Ffmcg-sector-outlook-growth-nielsen-18991571.htm%5C%22%3ENielsenIQ.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20December%20quarter%2C%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20grew%206.4%25%20in%20volumes%20on%20the%20back%20of%20positive%20consumption%20across%20the%20country%2C%20NielsenIQ%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rate%20of%20consumption%20growth%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20both%20volume%20and%20value%2C%20within%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20decelerated%20sequentially%20across%20the%20entire%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20was%20seen%20in%20both%20urban%20and%20rural%20markets%2C%20where%20volumes%20grew%20year-on-year%20but%20dipped%20sequentially%2C%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Findustry%2Fretail%2Ffmcg-industry-s-growth-this-year-could-halve-from-2023-says-nielseniq-11707206179710.html%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20urban%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%206.8%25%20as%20compared%20to%2010.2%25%20in%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20Rural%20volume%20growth%20stood%20at%205.8%25%20against%206.4%25%20in%20the%20July%20to%20September%20quarter%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EEconomic%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fretail.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Ffood-entertainment%2Fpersonal-care-pet-supplies-liquor%2Fdec-quarter-sees-6-4-surge-in-fmcg-volumes-urban-rural-gap-narrows-report%2F107455176%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20citing%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20value%20growth%20in%20the%20industry%20stood%20at%206%25%20in%20the%20quarter.%20This%20has%20been%20attributed%20to%20the%206.4%25%20rise%20in%20volume.%20Therefore%2C%20this%20indicates%20positive%20consumption%20patterns%20at%20an%20all-India%20level%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20also%20added%20that%20the%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20food%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%205.3%25%2C%20down%20from%208.7%25%20in%20the%20July-September%20quarter%20of%202023.%20This%20was%20attributed%20to%20the%20slowdown%20in%20the%20products%20under%20staples%20(such%20as%20refined%20and%20non-refined%20edible%20oils%2C%20etc.)%20and%20impulse%20(such%20as%20confectionery%2C%20etc.)%20categories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20non-food%20categories%2C%20which%20include%20personal%20and%20home%20care%20products%2C%20there%20is%20an%20improvement%2C%20with%20volume%20growth%20reaching%209.6%25%20in%20the%20quarter%20ended%20December%20as%20compared%20to%20last%20year.%20This%20is%20an%20increase%20from%20the%208.7%25%20recorded%20in%20July-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENote%20that%20growth%20in%20terms%20of%20volume%20refers%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20the%20physical%20quantity%20of%20goods%20sold%20over%20a%20specific%20period%2C%20irrespective%20of%20changes%20in%20pricing.%20This%20reflects%20the%20actual%20demand%20for%20the%20products.%20This%20aspect%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20consumer%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20growth%20in%20value%20terms%20refers%20to%20the%20increase%20in%20sales%20revenue%20or%20market%20value%20of%20FMCG%20products%20over%20a%20specific%20period.%20It%20takes%20into%20account%20factors%20such%20as%20price%20increases.%20It%20indicates%20how%20well%20a%20company%20is%20performing%20in%20terms%20of%20generating%20revenue%20from%20its%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENarrowing%20rural-urban%20gap%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20the%20anticipated%20slowdown%2C%20Nielsen%20remains%20optimistic%20about%20the%20FMCG%20industry%E2%80%99s%20prospects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERoosevelt%20Dsouza%2C%20head%20of%20customer%20success%20at%20NielsenIQ%20India%2C%20despite%20a%20sequential-quarter%20decline%2C%20the%20rural%20recovery%20narrative%20continued%20to%20evolve%20throughout%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20highlighted%20that%20in%202023%2C%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20consumption%20gaps%20between%20urban%20and%20rural%20markets%20narrowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20northern%20and%20western%20regions%20are%20contributing%20to%20this%20phenomenon.%20The%20favourable%20interim%20Union%20Budget%202024-25%2C%20supporting%20several%20economic%20boosters%20for%20the%20rural%20sector%2C%20should%20augur%20well%20for%20companies%20with%20a%20rural%20strategy%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dsouza%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20Q4%202023%2C%20we%20observe%20an%20uptick%20in%20consumption%2C%20primarily%20driven%20by%20habit-forming%20categories%20(such%20as%20biscuits%20and%20noodles)%20in%20food%20and%20essential%20home%20products.%20These%20categories%20have%20thrived%20despite%20flat%20to%20negative%20price%20growth%2C%20indicating%20resilience%20and%20sustained%20demand%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Frising-thali-cost-muted-fmcg-growth-booming-luxury-sales-why-the-k-shaped-recovery-still-stands%5C%22%3ERising%20Thali%20Cost%2C%20Muted%20Fmcg%20Growth%2C%20Booming%20Luxury%20Sales%3A%20Why%20the%20K-Shaped%20Recovery%20Still%20Stands%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20FMCG%20firms%20say%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20slowdown%20in%20rural%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Findustry%2Fretail%2Ffmcg-industry-s-growth-this-year-could-halve-from-2023-says-nielseniq-11707206179710.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20market%20analysts%20expressing%20their%20dissatisfaction%20with%20the%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFMCG%20companies%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20a%20persistent%20slowdown%20in%20rural%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20definite%20slowdown%2C%E2%80%9D%20Krishnarao%20Buddha%2C%20senior%20category%20head%2C%20marketing%20at%20Parle%20Products%20told%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20rural%20and%20urban%20markets%20have%20slowed%20down.%20Errant%20monsoon%20in%20select%20geographies%20due%20to%20the%20El%20Ni%C3%B1o%20has%20impacted%20slowdown%20in%20consumption.%20There%20is%20also%20a%20normalizing%20effect%20post-COVID%2C%E2%80%9D%20Buddha%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COverall%20sector%20growth%20continues%20to%20wane%2C%20with%20price%20growth%20turning%20negligible.%20Urban%20growth%20has%20seen%20moderation%20and%20is%20now%20growing%201.2X%20rural.%20The%20low%20base%20aids%20non-food%20volume%20recovery%2C%20while%20food%20categories%20are%20seeing%20volume%20growth%20moderation.%20Channel%20growth%20has%20moderated%2C%20but%20modern%20trade%20continues%20to%20clock%20healthy%20growth%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nitin%20Gupta%20of%20Emkay%20Global%20Financial%20Services%2C%20told%20the%20business%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%2C%20%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fmore-inventory-days-for-consumer-goods-as-low-demand-causes-supply-chain-congestion%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20persistent%20low%20demand%20in%20the%20FMCG%20sector%20is%20causing%20supply%20chain%20congestion%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20increase%20in%20inventory%20days%2C%20with%20stocks%20accumulating%20at%20distributors.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707305401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F15171005%2F1024px-Supermarket_full_of_goods.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffmcg-growth-slows-sequentially-in-december-quarter-expected-to-slow-to-4-5-6-5-in-2024-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20volume%20growth%20in%20the%20urban%20sector%20during%20the%20October-December%20quarter%20stood%20at%206.8%25%20as%20compared%20to%2010.2%25%20in%20the%20previous%20quarter.%20Rural%20volume%20growth%20stood%20at%205.8%25%20against%206.4%25%20in%20the%20July%20to%20September%20quarter.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffmcg-growth-slows-sequentially-in-december-quarter-expected-to-slow-to-4-5-6-5-in-2024-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump's%20New%20York%20criminal%20case%2C%20likely%20first%20for%20trial%2C%20faces%20crucial%20test%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707304468000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107492048%2Cimgsize-28406.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrumps-new-york-criminal-case-likely-first-for-trial-faces-crucial-test%2Farticleshow%2F107491869.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F107491869.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20first%20of%20four%20criminal%20cases%20against%20Donald%20Trump%20expected%20to%20go%20to%20trial%20faces%20a%20major%20test%20next%20week%2C%20when%20a%20New%20York%20judge%20is%20set%20to%20rule%20on%20the%20Republican%20former%20US%20president's%20bid%20that%20the%20case%20be%20tossed%20because%20it%20is%20partisan%20and%20not%20covered%20by%20state%20law.%20Trump%2C%20the%20frontrunner%20for%20the%202024%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%2C%20is%20scheduled%20to%20go%20on%20trial%20in%20state%20court%20in%20Manhattan%20starting%20March%2025%20on%20charges%20of%20falsifying%20business%20records%20to%20cover%20up%20a%20hush%20money%20payment%20to%20a%20porn%20star%20before%20the%202016%20election.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrumps-new-york-criminal-case-likely-first-for-trial-faces-crucial-test%2Farticleshow%2F107491869.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrumps-new-york-criminal-case-likely-first-for-trial-faces-crucial-test%2Famp_articleshow%2F107491869.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrumps-new-york-criminal-case-likely-first-for-trial-faces-crucial-test%2Famp_articleshow%2F107491869.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22ED%20Gathering%20Information%20on%20FDI%20Use%20in%20Paytm%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07151223%2Fimage-1813.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20is%20gathering%20information%20about%20the%20%E2%80%9Cend%20uses%E2%80%9D%20of%20foreign%20direct%20investment%20(FDI)%20in%20One97%20Communications%2C%20which%20owns%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20(PPB)%2C%20a%20source%20privy%20to%20the%20matter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.financialexpress.com%2Fbusiness%2Fbanking-finance-fdi-use-in-paytm-under-enforcement-directorate-lens-3386712%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20exercise%20is%20to%20ascertain%20if%20the%20foreign%20funds%20were%20used%20for%20investments%20other%20than%20those%20stated%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%2C%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20FDI%20is%20not%20subject%20to%20rigourous%20end-use%20norms%2C%20but%20foreign%20capital%20raised%20by%20Indian%20companies%20through%20the%20ADR-GDR%20route%20aren%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20to%20be%20invested%20in%20real%20estate%20or%20stock%20markets.%20The%20regulations%20are%20principally%20governed%20by%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20(FEMA)%2C%20%3Cem%3EFE%3C%2Fem%3E%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20told%20the%20newspaper%20that%20the%20ED%20is%20%E2%80%9Conly%20enquiring%20into%20the%20process%E2%80%9D%20(of%20end-uses%20of%20FDI)%20received%20by%20One97%2C%20while%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20yet%20ventured%20into%20an%20%E2%80%9Cinvestigation%E2%80%9D%20into%20the%20matter%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20for%20Paytm%20told%20news%20agencies%20that%20allegations%20regarding%20FEMA%20violations%20were%20%E2%80%9Cunfounded%20and%20factually%20incorrect%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20according%20to%20Reuters%2C%20CEO%20Vijay%20Shekhar%20Sharma%20and%20other%20Paytm%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fbanking%2Ffinance%2Fpaytm-ceo-vijay-shekhar-sharma-officials-meet-rbi-to-discuss-regulatory-concerns-sources%2Farticleshow%2F107448106.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Emet%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20senior%20RBI%20executives%20on%20February%206%20(Tuesday)%20to%20deliberate%20on%20%E2%80%9Ca%20road%20map%20to%20address%20regulatory%20concerns.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20Sharma%20also%20met%20finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20at%20the%20Parliament%20building.%20Sources%20told%20the%20business%20daily%20that%20the%20government%20clarified%20it%20has%20no%20role%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20falls%20within%20the%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%2034%20foreign%20(FDI)%20investors%20hold%20a%20little%20over%2045%25%20in%20One97%20Communications%2C%20and%20over%20450%20FPIs%20together%20have%20a%2018.64%25%20stake%20in%20the%20firm.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20shares%20are%20with%20Sharma%20(9.1%25)%2C%20retail%20investors%20(12.85%25)%2C%20mutual%20funds%20(4.99%25)%2C%20body%20corporates%20(6.33%25)%20and%20others%2C%20the%20newspaper%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20FDI%20rules%2C%2049%25%20FDI%20under%20the%20automatic%20route%20is%20allowed%20in%20the%20private%20banking%20sector%2C%20extendable%20up%20to%2074%25%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20the%20government%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFDI%20in%20fintechs%20are%20governed%20by%20separate%20guidelines%20issued%20by%20the%20RBI%2C%20governing%20electronic%20payments%2C%20know-your-customer%20requirements%20and%20data%20localisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20told%20%3Cem%3EFE%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20ED%20is%20investigating%20another%20aspect%2C%20which%20pertains%20to%20whether%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20has%20facilitated%20any%20transactions%20that%20contributed%20to%20money%20laundering.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20RBI%20has%20clearly%20prohibited%20PPB%20from%20offshore%20transactions%2C%20but%20if%20the%20platform%20was%20used%20for%20the%20purpose%2C%20then%20it%20has%20to%20be%20seen%20whether%20money%20laundering%20was%20the%20reason%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20source%2C%20asking%20not%20to%20be%20identified%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EFE.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20pre-registered%20scheduled%20offence%20under%20PMLA%20as%20on%20date%2C%20but%20this%20is%20not%20an%20impediment%20for%20the%20agency%20to%20begin%20a%20probe%20under%20PMLA%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%20has%20directed%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20to%20stop%20allowing%20deposits%20into%20customers%E2%80%99%20accounts%20after%20February%2029%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Frbi-paytm-payment-bank-action%5C%22%3Eciting%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cpersistent%20non-compliances%E2%80%9D.%20The%20services%20barred%20include%20using%20the%20United%20Payments%20Interface%20(UPI)%2C%20IMPS%2C%20Aadhaar-enabled%20payments%20and%20bill%20payment%20transactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707303620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F07151223%2Fimage-1813.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-gathering-information-on-fdi-use-in-paytm-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20exercise%20is%20to%20ascertain%20if%20the%20foreign%20funds%20were%20used%20for%20investments%20other%20than%20those%20stated%20to%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20the%20'Financial%20Express'%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-gathering-information-on-fdi-use-in-paytm-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kremlin%20confirms%20Putin%20has%20given%20interview%20to%20ex-Fox%20News%20host%20Tucker%20Carlson%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707302580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-tucker-carlson-vladimir-putin_6447253.jpg%3F20240207110216%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Ftucker-carlson-kremlin-confirms-putin-gav