3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSchool%20was%20no%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20this%20trauma%20and%20abuse%20was%20affecting%20my%20growth.%20I%20was%20not%20good%20at%20academics%20and%20I%20did%20not%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20friends.%20All%20I%20had%20in%20school%20was%20bullies%20and%20abuse.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20the%20constant%20abuse%20led%20her%20to%20believe%20that%20it%20was%20something%20she%20deserved.%20%E2%80%9CAbuse%20became%20my%20normal%20and%20comfort%20zone.%20These%20experiences%20primed%20me%20for%20dissociation.%20Even%20now%2C%20I%20can%20easily%20slip%20into%20a%20mental%20space%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20fully%20present%2C%20where%20my%20body%20and%20mind%20disconnect.%20This%20dissociation%20is%20one%20of%20the%20lasting%20effects%20of%20abuse.%20Surprisingly%2C%20it%20led%20me%20towards%20more%20such%20instances%20in%20my%20life%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFinding%20myself%20and%20breaking%20the%20cycle%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20remember%20in%20school%2C%20I%20tried%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20a%20teacher%20when%20I%20was%2015.%20It%20took%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20strength%20to%20open%20up%2C%20but%20she%20did%20not%20believe%20me.%20She%20judged%20me%20for%20being%20a%20poor%20student%20and%20thought%20I%20was%20just%20making%20excuses%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20disaster.%20The%20rejection%20pushed%20me%20deeper%20into%20isolation.%20I%20remember%20having%20a%20full-blown%20breakdown%20in%20school.%20Things%20were%20bad%20and%20every%20small%20abuse%20would%20push%20me%20closer%20to%20the%20edge.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20how%20these%20experiences%20affected%20her%20as%20a%20young%20adult%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CUnconsciously%2C%20we%20tend%20to%20repeat%20what%E2%80%99s%20familiar%20to%20us.%20Growing%20up%20in%20an%20environment%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20conducive%20to%20a%20healthy%20childhood%2C%20I%20found%20myself%20mirroring%20this%20chaos%20in%20my%20relationships%2C%20particularly%20in%20friendships.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20eventually%20married%20a%20partner%20who%20proved%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F45514%2Fdomestic-violence-law-india-women-harrassment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eextremely%20abusive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20abuse%20began%20during%20my%20teenage%20years%20when%20I%20met%20him%20in%20college.%20Initially%2C%20it%20started%20subtly%2C%20perhaps%20with%20a%20mild%20action%20like%20him%20pressing%20my%20neck%2C%20pushing%20me%2C%20or%20tightening%20his%20grip.%20Strangely%2C%20I%20never%20identified%20it%20as%20abuse%20because%2C%20for%20me%2C%20these%20actions%20were%20normalised%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abused%20at%20home%2C%20Mansi%20started%20to%20push%20herself%20into%20a%20shell%20and%20had%20almost%20no%20friends%20in%20school.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-2-1706795923-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-340547%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAbused%20at%20home%2C%20Mansi%20started%20to%20push%20herself%20into%20a%20shell%20and%20had%20almost%20no%20friends%20in%20school.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPondering%20how%20the%20mind%20of%20an%20abuse%20survivor%20works%2C%20she%20says%20that%20it%20would%20lead%20her%20to%20believe%20that%20everything%20was%20her%20fault.%20%E2%80%9CWhenever%20someone%20treated%20me%20wrongly%2C%20I%20would%20always%20find%20ways%20to%20justify%20it.%20I%20thought%20that%20maybe%20they%E2%80%99re%20struggling%2C%20perhaps%20something%20is%20going%20on%20for%20them%2C%20or%20maybe%20I%20inadvertently%20offended%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMansi%20recalls%20how%20she%20needed%20someone%20to%20tell%20her%20that%20this%20was%20abuse.%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20a%20few%20people%20and%20friends%20that%20would%20constantly%20remind%20me%20of%20how%20abusive%20my%20relationship%20was.%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20out%20of%20it%2C%20but%20for%20years%2C%20I%20did%20not%20know%20how%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20finally%20take%20the%20leap%20and%20divorce%20her%20husband.%20%E2%80%9CThings%20were%20getting%20out%20of%20hand%20and%20I%20decided%20to%20leave.%20It%20was%20during%20this%20time%20that%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20therapy%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20therapy%20changed%20her%20life%20in%20many%20ways.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20for%20a%20brief%20time%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20huge%20step%20for%20me.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20express%20what%20was%20inside%20for%20so%20long.%20This%20was%2C%20in%20a%20way%2C%20the%20starting%20point%20for%20my%20journey%20towards%20betterment%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20therapy%2C%20Mansi%20also%20realised%20how%20she%20was%20a%20good%20listener%20to%20other%20people.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20sure%20if%20it%20was%20because%20I%20was%20going%20through%20so%20much%20that%20made%20me%20empathetic%20to%20people%E2%80%99s%20suffering.%20People%20would%20come%20to%20me%20and%20tell%20me%20about%20their%20issues.%20I%20would%20never%20give%20them%20advice%20but%20always%20listened%20to%20them%20attentively%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELater%20she%20decided%20to%20go%20to%20NYU%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F317508%2Fbengal-dr-girindrasekhar-bose-first-indian-psychoanalyst-sigmund-freud-mental-health-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%20psychology.%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9CI%20applied%20for%20a%20master%E2%80%99s%20and%20after%20graduating%2C%20I%20started%20a%20small%20practice%20in%20the%20US.%20In%202012%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20come%20back%20to%20India%20with%20my%20current%20partner%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHealing%20is%20not%20linear%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Presently%2C%20Mansi%20is%20a%20therapist%20helping%20people%20heal%20from%20trauma%20with%20her%20foundation.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-3-1706795935-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-340548%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPresently%2C%20Mansi%20is%20a%20therapist%20helping%20people%20heal%20from%20trauma%20through%20her%20foundation.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrauma%20holds%20in%20your%20body%20in%20different%20ways%20and%20comes%20out%20in%20outbursts.%20Taking%20therapy%20and%20studying%20psychology%20helped%20Mansi%20understand%20herself%20better.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20only%20when%20I%20delved%20into%20the%20study%20of%20trauma%20and%20immersed%20myself%20in%20that%20work%20that%20I%20became%20aware%20of%20the%20extent%20of%20trauma%20I%20carry%20within%20me.%20It%20manifested%20as%20rage%20outbursts%2C%20struggles%20with%20substance%20abuse%2C%20and%20eating%20issues%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTrauma%20manifested%20in%20various%20ways%20in%20my%20life.%20In%20my%2020s%2C%20I%20battled%20an%20eating%20disorder%2C%20struggling%20with%20bulimia.%20I%20was%20battling%20something%2C%20I%20did%20not%20even%20know%20existed%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReturning%20home%2C%20she%20realised%20how%20there%20were%20so%20many%20people%20who%20went%20through%20the%20same%20things%20as%20her.%20%E2%80%9CI%20realised%20that%20what%20happened%20to%20me%20is%20more%20common%20than%20you%20can%20imagine.%20I%20wanted%20to%20help%20them%20heal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F337049%2Fitc-fiama-mental-health-survey-therapy-counselling-support-gen-z-millennials-parents%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETherapy%20was%20not%20very%20popular%3C%2Fa%3E%20back%20then%20and%20she%20found%20it%20very%20difficult%20to%20get%20a%20job%20anywhere.%20%E2%80%9CI%20noticed%20that%20while%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20graduates%20of%20psychology%2C%20there%20was%20no%20place%20for%20them%20to%20start%20their%20careers.%20This%20is%20how%20the%20Heal%20Grow%20Thrive%20Foundation%20came%20into%20being.%20Since%20we%20are%20self-funded%2C%20the%20therapy%20is%20done%20for%20a%20small%20fee%20but%20what%20we%20focus%20on%20is%20healing%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20fleet%20of%2020%20young%20and%20budding%20therapists%2C%20she%20has%20helped%20over%20500%20survivors%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20patient%20of%20Mansi%20who%20prefers%20to%20be%20anonymous%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20first%20talked%20to%20Mansi%2C%20she%20created%20a%20safe%20space%20for%20me.%20It%20was%20a%20space%20where%20I%20could%20really%20be%20%E2%80%98me%E2%80%99.%20I%20did%20not%20understand%20how%20much%20I%20needed%20the%20help%20until%20I%20took%20it.%20The%20best%20thing%20is%20that%20she%20focussed%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98why%E2%80%99%20instead%20of%20turning%20to%20medication.%20Why%20was%20I%20feeling%20a%20certain%20way%2C%20why%20is%20the%20trauma%20so%20deeply%20rooted%2C%20and%20what%20I%20can%20do%20to%20help%20myself%3F%20I%20am%20glad%20that%20I%20took%20the%20step%20for%20myself.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMansi%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20main%20focal%20point%20of%20my%20practice%20is%20to%20heal%20by%20processing%20things.%20As%20a%20survivor%20and%20a%20psychologist%2C%20I%20know%20how%20taking%20medicine%20can%20feel%20like%20a%20way%20out.%20However%2C%20I%20sincerely%20believe%20in%20trying%20everything%20in%20my%20power%20before%20referring%20patients%20to%20a%20psychiatrist.%20We%20believe%20in%20creating%20a%20safe%20space%20for%20the%20trauma%20survivor%20and%20helping%20them%20heal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20how%20healing%20is%20not%20linear%2C%20she%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20I%20am%20an%20adult%20out%20of%20that%20house%20and%20all%20the%20trauma%20it%20brought%2C%20I%20still%20get%20stuck%20in%20toxic%20cycles.%20I%20am%20happy%20that%20I%20am%20away%20from%20it%2C%20but%20I%20still%20believe%20that%20healing%20is%20not%20linear%20and%20you%20can%20always%20slip%20back.%20I%20still%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20isolate%20myself%20and%20disassociate%20from%20my%20body.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1Ujj20yvra%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1Ujj20yvra%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC1Ujj20yvra%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Mansi%20Poddar%7C%20Psychotherapist%20(%40healwithmansi)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20what%20is%20important%20is%20the%20first%20step%20towards%20healing.%20Once%20you%20reach%20there%2C%20you%20will%20start%20to%20get%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20anyone%20who%20is%20suffering%20as%20she%20did%20in%20the%20past%2C%20Mansi%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20believe%2C%20more%20than%20anything%2C%20that%20parents%20should%20read%20and%20comprehend%20the%20importance%20of%20not%20stigmatising%20mental%20health.%20It%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20for%20parents%20to%20advocate%20for%20their%20kids%2C%20not%20necessarily%20through%20confrontations%20with%20teachers%20and%20others%2C%20but%20by%20genuinely%20sitting%20down%20with%20their%20children%20and%20understanding%20their%20perspective.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20message%20is%20directed%20towards%20parents%2C%20teachers%2C%20and%20adults%20in%20general%2C%20urging%20them%20to%20become%20more%20trauma-informed.%20It%E2%80%99s%20essential%20to%20recognise%20what%20might%20be%20traumatic%20for%20a%20child%20and%20to%20avoid%20hindering%20their%20access%20to%20mental%20health%20care.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Edited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20%3Cem%3EAll%20pictures%20courtesy%3A%20Mansi%20Poddar)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706797215000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2Fmansi-1-1706795794.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D340517%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mansi%20Poddar%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20therapist%2C%20survived%20domestic%20violence%2C%20molestation%20and%20abuse.%20With%20her%20Heal%20Grow%20Thrive%20Foundation%2C%20she%20helps%20survivors%20heal%20from%20their%20trauma.%20In%20a%20candid%20conversation%2C%20Mansi%20shares%20her%20experiences%20and%20the%20lessons%20she%20learned.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Tina%20Freese%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22TechForGood%20India%20Conclave%3A%20Highlighting%20the%20Importance%20of%20Collaboration%20%26amp%3B%20Technology%20To%20Accelerate%20SDGs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20sponsored%20by%20nasscom%20foundation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20global%20vision%20to%20foster%20peace%20and%20progress%20around%20the%20world%2C%20in%202015%2C%20all%20the%20United%20Nations%20member%20states%20embraced%20the%202030%20Agenda%20for%20Sustainable%20Development.%20With%20its%2017%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals%20(SDGs)%2C%20the%20agenda%20sets%20forth%20imperative%20tasks%20that%20demand%20collaborative%20efforts%20to%20tackle%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20challenges.%20Within%20these%20goals%20lie%20not%20only%20significant%20challenges%20but%20also%20unprecedented%20opportunities%20for%20businesses%2C%20governments%2C%20and%20communities%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmphasising%20the%20universal%20nature%20of%20the%20issue%2C%20it%20is%20pivotal%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20addressing%20the%20decline%20in%20SDG%20progress%20necessitates%20collective%20attention%20and%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUnless%20we%20act%20now%2C%20the%202030%20Agenda%20will%20become%20an%20epitaph%20for%20a%20world%20that%20might%20have%20been%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20UN%20Secretary-General%20Ant%C3%B3nio%20Guterres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAligning%20with%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%202030%20SDG%20Agenda%2C%20the%20NASSCOM%20Foundation%20recently%20organised%20the%20TechForGood%20India%20Conclave%202024%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20Focused%20on%20the%20theme%20%E2%80%98Accelerating%20the%202030%20Agenda%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329369%2Ficse-2023-mobius-foundation-achieve-sustainable-development-goals-through-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESustainable%20Development%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethrough%20Technology%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20event%20brought%20together%20civil%20society%2C%20social%20innovators%2C%20entrepreneurs%2C%20government%20representatives%2C%20and%20technology%20and%20development%20leaders%20to%20collaborate%20on%20accelerating%20India%E2%80%99s%20SDG%20objectives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20covered%20essential%20topics%20such%20as%20sustainable%20living%2C%20climate%20action%2C%20healthcare%2C%20education%2C%20and%20empowering%20women%20entrepreneurs.%20The%20event%20included%20engaging%20masterc